    <fr:display-uri>opt-6010</fr:display-uri>
    <fr:route>/opt-6010/</fr:route>
    <fr:title text="Derivation of the First-order Variation">Derivation of the First-order Variation</fr:title>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <html:p>
    We derive <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\frac {\partial  J}{\partial  \mathbf {u}}]]></fr:tex> for the <fr:link href="/opt-6002/" title="Bolza Problem" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/opt-6002/" display-uri="opt-6002" type="local">Bolza problem</fr:link> from first principles, then show how the <fr:link href="/opt-6009/" title="Costate Equation" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/opt-6009/" display-uri="opt-6009" type="local">costate</fr:link> arises naturally.
</html:p>
    <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
      <fr:frontmatter>
        <fr:authors>
          <fr:author>
            <fr:link href="/boat/" title="Zihang Zeng" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/boat/" display-uri="boat" type="local">Zihang Zeng</fr:link>
          </fr:author>
        </fr:authors>
        <fr:date>
          <fr:year>2026</fr:year>
          <fr:month>3</fr:month>
          <fr:day>7</fr:day>
        </fr:date>
        <fr:title text="Linearization of J">Linearization of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[J]]></fr:tex></fr:title>
      </fr:frontmatter>
      <fr:mainmatter>
        <html:p>
      Expanding <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[J(\mathbf {u} + \Delta  \mathbf {u}) - J(\mathbf {u})]]></fr:tex> to first order:
  </html:p>
        <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
      \int _0^{t_f} \frac {\partial  L}{\partial  \mathbf {x}} \Delta  \mathbf {x} \, dt + \int _0^{t_f} \frac {\partial  L}{\partial  \mathbf {u}} \Delta  \mathbf {u} \, dt + \frac {d\Phi }{d\mathbf {x}}\left ( \mathbf {x}(t_f) \right ) \Delta  \mathbf {x}(t_f)
  ]]></fr:tex>
      </fr:mainmatter>
    </fr:tree>
    <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
      <fr:frontmatter>
        <fr:authors>
          <fr:author>
            <fr:link href="/boat/" title="Zihang Zeng" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/boat/" display-uri="boat" type="local">Zihang Zeng</fr:link>
          </fr:author>
        </fr:authors>
        <fr:date>
          <fr:year>2026</fr:year>
          <fr:month>3</fr:month>
          <fr:day>7</fr:day>
        </fr:date>
        <fr:title text="Variation of the state">Variation of the state</fr:title>
      </fr:frontmatter>
      <fr:mainmatter>
        <html:p>
      Linearizing the dynamics <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\dot {\mathbf {x}} = f(\mathbf {x}, \mathbf {u})]]></fr:tex> gives
  </html:p>
        <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\dot {\Delta  \mathbf {x}}(t) = \frac {\partial  f}{\partial  \mathbf {x}} \Delta  \mathbf {x}(t) + \frac {\partial  f}{\partial  \mathbf {u}} \Delta  \mathbf {u}(t)]]></fr:tex>
        <html:p>
      whose solution, with <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Delta  \mathbf {x}(0) = 0]]></fr:tex>, is
  </html:p>
        <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\Delta  \mathbf {x}(t) = \int _0^{t} \Psi (t, \tau ) \frac {\partial  f}{\partial  \mathbf {u}}\left ( \mathbf {x}(\tau ), \mathbf {u}(\tau ) \right ) \Delta  \mathbf {u}(\tau ) \, d\tau ]]></fr:tex>
        <html:p>
      where <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Psi (t, \tau )]]></fr:tex> is the state transition matrix of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\frac {\partial  f}{\partial  \mathbf {x}}]]></fr:tex>.
  </html:p>
      </fr:mainmatter>
    </fr:tree>
    <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
      <fr:frontmatter>
        <fr:authors>
          <fr:author>
            <fr:link href="/boat/" title="Zihang Zeng" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/boat/" display-uri="boat" type="local">Zihang Zeng</fr:link>
          </fr:author>
        </fr:authors>
        <fr:date>
          <fr:year>2026</fr:year>
          <fr:month>3</fr:month>
          <fr:day>7</fr:day>
        </fr:date>
        <fr:title text="Collecting \Delta  \mathbf {u} terms">Collecting <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Delta  \mathbf {u}]]></fr:tex> terms</fr:title>
      </fr:frontmatter>
      <fr:mainmatter>
        <html:p>
      Substituting <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Delta  \mathbf {x}]]></fr:tex> and swapping integration order (Fubini), all three terms become inner products against <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Delta  \mathbf {u}(\tau )]]></fr:tex>, yielding
  </html:p>
        <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
      \left ( \frac {\partial  J}{\partial  \mathbf {u}}(\tau ) \right )^\intercal  = \underbrace {\left ( \int _\tau ^{t_f} \frac {\partial  L}{\partial  \mathbf {x}} \Psi (t, \tau ) \, dt + \frac {d\Phi }{d\mathbf {x}}\left ( \mathbf {x}(t_f) \right ) \Psi (t_f, \tau ) \right )}_{\mathbf {p}^\intercal (\tau )} \frac {\partial  f}{\partial  \mathbf {u}}\left ( \mathbf {x}(\tau ), \mathbf {u}(\tau ) \right ) + \left ( \frac {\partial  L}{\partial  \mathbf {u}}\left ( \mathbf {x}(\tau ), \mathbf {u}(\tau ) \right ) \right )^\intercal 
  ]]></fr:tex>
        <html:p>
      The bracketed expression is precisely the <fr:link href="/opt-6009/" title="Costate Equation" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/opt-6009/" display-uri="opt-6009" type="local">costate</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {p}(\tau )]]></fr:tex>, so we recover
  </html:p>
        <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\frac {\partial  J}{\partial  \mathbf {u}} = \left ( \frac {\partial  f}{\partial  \mathbf {u}} \right )^\intercal  \mathbf {p} + \left ( \frac {\partial  L}{\partial  \mathbf {u}} \right )^\intercal ]]></fr:tex>
      </fr:mainmatter>
    </fr:tree>
  </fr:mainmatter>
  <fr:backmatter>
